The paper discusses the use of oracles in superintelligent AI systems and their alignment with long-term research goals of AI safety. It specifically focuses on computer algebra systems (CASs) and their integration with theorem provers, which falls under the category of automated theorem proving (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses architectural deficiencies in CASs, which relates to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and scientific computing (cs.SC). Overall, the paper's focus on AI safety and the integration of CASs with theorem provers suggests that the most likely sub-category is cs.AI.
